{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = 1985: What Happens After Big Brother Dies | image = 1985 What Happens After Big Brother Dies.jpg<!-- include the file, px and alt: [[File:Example.jpg|200px|Cover]] --> | image_caption = | author = György Dalos | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = Hungarian, English | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = Pantheon Books | pub_date = 1983 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = | isbn = 0394537807 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = [[1984 (novel)|1984]]| followed_by = }}
'''''1985''''' is a sequel to [[George Orwell|George Orwell's]] novel ''[[Nineteen Eighty-Four]]''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/1985-What-Happens-After-Brother/dp/0394537807|title=1985: What Happens After Big Brother Dies|last=Dalos|first=György|date=1983|publisher=Pantheon Books|isbn=9780394537801|location=New York|language=English}}</ref>
Written by [[Hungary|Hungarian]] author [[György Dalos]], originally published in 1983, this novel begins with the death of [[Big Brother (Nineteen Eighty-Four)|Big Brother]] and reflects an intermediate period between 1984 and a more optimistic future characterized with a decline in orthodoxy of the totalitarian system, struggles of the ensuing powers and the near destruction of the [[Oceania (Nineteen Eighty-Four)|Oceania]] air force by [[Eurasia (Nineteen Eighty-Four)|Eurasia]].
