{{Infobox language family |name=Bushoong |ethnicity= |region= |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C.80]]) |fam6=[[Bangi–Tetela languages|Bangi–Tetela]]? |glotto=bush1251 |glottoname=Bushoong–Wongo–Lele |glotto2=song1305 |glottoname2=Songomeno }}
The '''Bushoong languages''' are a clade of [[Bantu language]]s coded Zone C.80 in Guthrie's classification. According to Nurse & Philippson (2003), apart from [[Dengese language|Dengese]] and the [[Shuwa language|Shuwa]] "dialect" of Bushoong, the languages form a valid node. They are: : [[Hendo language|Hendo]] (Songomeno), [[Bushoong language|Bushoong]], [[Lele language (Bantu)|Lele]], [[Wongo language|Wongo]]
