'''Jwaneng Airport''' {{airport codes|JWA|FBJW}} is an airport serving [[Jwaneng]], a town in the [[Southern District (Botswana)|Southern District]] of [[Botswana]]. It is owned by [[Debswana]], which also owns the [[Jwaneng diamond mine]]. There is no scheduled airline service.
The Jwaneng [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''JWN''') is located on the field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/JWN/Jwaneng_NDB_BW/#lat=-24.60070037841797,lon=24.68589973449707,zoom=10,type=Satellite|title=Jwaneng NDB (JWN) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
