{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --> | name = The Evpatoria Report | image = Theevpatoriareport.jpg | caption = | image_size = <!-- Only for images narrower than 220 pixels --> | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = Switzerland | instrument = | genre = [[Post-rock]] | years_active = 2002–2008, 2015- present | label = Shayo Records | associated_acts = | website = [http://the-evpatoria-report.bandcamp.com http://the-evpatoria-report.bandcamp.com/] | current_members = Laurent Quint, Simon, Dilo, Fabrice, Daniel Bacsinszky | past_members = }} '''The Evpatoria Report''' is a [[Swiss]] [[post-rock]] band. The band was formed in January 2002, and it consists of two guitarists, a bassist, a drummer, and a violinist/keyboardist. The Evpatoria Report have played concerts in [[Paris]] and toured throughout [[Switzerland]], playing with bands such as [[Red Sparowes]], [[The Appleseed Cast]], and [[Mono (Japanese band)|Mono]].<ref>{{cite web|last= |first= |url=http://www.darksite.ch/shayo/theevpatoriareport.html |title=THE EVPATORIA REPORT |website=darksite.ch |accessdate=April 21, 2016}}</ref> The band was on a hiatus from 2008 until they announced their return to the studio in April 2015.
==History== [[File:70-м антенна П-2500 (РТ-70).jpg|thumb|70-m aerial P-2500 (RT-70 radio telescope) in Yevpatoria.]] The band was formed in January 2002 and is named for the [[Crimea|Crimean]] city [[Yevpatoria]] ([[Romanization of Russian|romanized]] from [[Russian language| Russian]] as Evpatoria), in which the radio telescope [[Yevpatoria RT-70 radio telescope|RT-70]] P-2500 is located. It sends messages into space, including [[A Message From Earth]] and [[Cosmic Call]], that try to describe human life or "the Evpatoria message".<ref>{{cite web|author=Jonas |url=http://thesilentballet.com/reviews/Interview__The_Evpatoria_Report.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421133758/http://thesilentballet.com/reviews/Interview__The_Evpatoria_Report.html |archive-date=April 21, 2016 |title=Interview: The Evpatoria Report |website=thesilentballet.com|accessdate=April 21, 2016}}</ref>
==Members== * Laurent Quint – guitar * Simon Robert – guitar * David Di Lorenzo – bass * Fabrice Berney – drums, glockenspiel * Daniel Bacsinszky – violin, keyboard
